The Dockerfile does not execute any CMake build commands. It only clones the repository and sets the working directory. To successfully build espeak-ng, add CMake build commands after setting the working directory. For example: RUN ./autogen.sh && ./configure && make -j$(nproc) or RUN cmake -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release && cmake --build build --parallel. Also ensure the build.sh script referenced in COPY command contains proper build instructions.